Introduction
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
RGG aka Reactor Geometry Generator program is a tool to generate assembly geometry in OpenCascase or ACIS format using CGM (ITAPS, ANL).
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

In order to use rgg program use standard autotools commands:
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
autoreconf -fi;
./configure --with-igeom=/homes/jain/lib/CGM-acis --enable-debug;
cd rgg_source; 
make nrgen_test; 
nrgen_test;
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Launch the executable 'nrgen_test' from the rgg directory as follows
usage: nrgen_test <inpufile name.inp> <o/p file name .sat>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

EXAMPLE (Sample input files can be found in files directory in rgg)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
nrgen_test ./files/s1.inp ./files/s1.sat
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Note: .sat is created when compiled with CGM based on ACIS, use .brep when compiled with CGM based on OCC

v1.inp has the following lines:
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
! #############################################################################################################
! Hexagonal VHTR Control Fuel Block Assembly Definition without CellMaterials (Prism) around individual Pins
! #############################################################################################################
!
GeometryType Hexagonal  ! Card Card_Data    - GeometryType Hexagonal/Cartesian
!                                     
Materials 6 Mat_Coolant C1 Mat_Fuel  F1 Mat_Block G1 Mat_Poison P1 Mat_Control R1 Mat_FHH H1  !'Materials' Material No_of_Materials Name Alias
!
Dimensions 2 0.0 0.0 -0 793.0 36.0 37.3  G1 C1 ! 'Dimensions' No._of_blocks center_of_blocks(X,Y) Zstart Zend Pitch_of_blocks Alias_of_blocks
!
Pincells 8 1.87960 ! 'Pincells' No_of_pincells pitch
! 1
Cell_Fuel       FC 1 !Pincell_Name Pincell_Alias No_of_Lines_to_define_pincell
Cylinder  2 0.0 0.0    0.0 793.0   0.6225 0.6350 F1 C1  ! 'Cylinder' No_of_cylinders center_of_cylinder(X,Y) Zstart Zend Radii_of_Cylinders Material_Alias
! 2
Cell_BurnPoison BP 1
Cylinder  2 0.0 0.0    0.0 793.0   0.6225 0.6350 P1 C1
! 3
Cell_SmallCoolant    SC 1
Cylinder  1 0.0 0.0    0.0 793.0   0.6350 C1
! 4
Cell_Coolant    CC 1
Cylinder  1 0.0 0.0    0.0 793.0   0.79375 C1
! 5
Cell_FuelHandle FH 0
! 6
Cell_Graphite   GC 0
! 7
AVol_Control CR 1                                         
Cylinder  3  0.0 0.0 0.0 793.0 2.64 4.13 4.7625 C1 R1 C1 
! 8
AVol_FHH     FH2 1
Cylinder  1  0.0 0.0 0.0 793.0 2.0 H1   
!                  
Assembly 11    ! 'Assembly' No_of_pincells_on_flat_side                                             
                     BP  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  BP
                   FC  CC  FC  FC  GC  GC  GC  GC  FC  FC  CC  FC
                 CC  FC  FC  CC  GC  GC  GC  GC  GC  CC  FC  FC  CC
               FC  FC  CC  FC  GC  GC  GC  GC  GC  GC  FC  CC  FC  FC
             FC  CC  FC  FC  GC  GC  GC  CR  GC  GC  GC  FC  FC  CC  FC
           CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  GC  GC  GC  GC  GC  GC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC
         FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  GC  GC  GC  GC  GC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC
       FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  GC  GC  GC  GC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC
     CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  SC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC
   FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  SC  FH  FH  SC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC
 BP  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FH  FH2  FH  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  BP
   FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  SC  FH  FH  SC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC
     CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  SC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC
       FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC
         FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC
           CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC
             FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC
               FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC
                 CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC
                   FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC
                     BP  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  FC  CC  FC  BP
END ! This is a must
